      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>Probably by rearchitecting your entire app.  Client server is not an effective architecture on Android.  Services do not last forever.  Even foreground services will eventually be killed on purpose by the OS.  Do not expect processes to continue on Android when not in the foreground.  It's against the entire design of the OS where it explicitly tries to prevent this behavior for battery life.  Instead, explain why you think you need that, and we may be able to tell you how to write your app to avoid needing it at all-  there are lots of ways to drive behavior on demand in Android rather than keeping a service around.</p>\n",
