          "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
          "body": "@JessyJamesstandswithRussia You just cannot rely on a constantly running service of any sort on Android.  You need to find alternatives, such as using push messaging to notify the app that there is a call available.  Even if you could rely on it, it wouldn&#39;t work in Doze mode (the mode the phone enters when the screen is off for a while and almost all processing is killed to preserve battery life)."
